SED (Streamline Editor)

Delete the lines
Substitutes the lines
add the lines

Sed will not change file and print the changes on the terminal, this is the default behavior of SED

SED (Deleting The lines)

sed -e '/root/ d' /tmp/passwd
sed -i -e '/root/ d' /tmp/passwd
sed -i -e'/1 d' /tmp/passwd

SED (Substituting  The words)
 
sed -e 's/root/ROOT/' /tmp/passwd
sed -i -e 's/root/ROOT' /tmp/passwd
sed -i -e 's/root/ROOT/gi' /tmp/passwd